%I A397304 #5 Jun 25 2026 19:19:08
%S A397304 408,538,792,984
%N A397304 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that sigma(x)^3*psi(x) = x^4 + y^4 + z^4 + t^4 + w^4.
%C A397304 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma^3*psi-quartic quintuple.
%H A397304 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%H A397304 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-3-psi-quartic-quintuples/blob/main/A397304">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A397304 (408, 184, 216, 832, 872) is such a quintuple because sigma(408)^3 * psi(408) = 1080^3 * 864 = 408^4 + 184^4 + 216^4 + 832^4 + 872^4.
%o A397304 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A397304 Cf. A000203, A001615, A386225, A391536.
%K A397304 nonn,hard,more
%O A397304 1,1
%A A397304 _S. I. Dimitrov_, Jun 20 2026
